docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, July 29 The head of the United States Alliance for Progress Program, Teodoro Moscoso, has told his staff here and in Latin-American centers that there will be no "celebration" of the Alliance's first anniversary next month because the results so far do not warrant one. The occasion will be noted without fanfare.
docs.abstract: Moscoso bars celebration of 1st anniv of Alliance Aug 17, memo to staff; cites 'spotty' progress and 'frustrating' obstacles; hopes '63 anniv will be worth celebrating

headline.main: Chief of Alliance for Progress Bars Anniversary Celebration
